thread.title: British police investigating suspicious substance at parliament

author: Reuters Editorial
title: British police investigating suspicious substance at parliament
text: March 12, 2018 / 2:26 PM / in 11 minutes Suspicious substance at UK parliament was not hazardous: spokesman Reuters Staff 1 Min Read LONDON (Reuters) - A suspicious substance sent to a building at the British parliament was found to be non-hazardous, a spokesman for parliament said on Monday. “Today a suspicious substance was investigated by the Met Police and was found not to be hazardous,” the parliamentary spokesman said in a statement. Two people were taken to hospital as a precaution. Reporting by William James; writing by Alistair Smout; editing by Michael Holden
